commit.message: Disable AppVeyor tests while cram is broken on Windows
Install pytest 5.4.3 in AppVeyor, upgrade setuptools

Travis: test with pytest 5.4.3

pytest-cram 0.2.1 is incompatible with pytest 6.0.

DOC no need to specify files in pre-commit example

There is already
```
types: [jupyter]
```
in `.pre-commit-hooks.yaml`
Bump version: 0.3.8 → 0.3.9
Update changelog
Apply pre-commit hook to files of type Jupyter

Add --extra-keys flag to pass extra keys to strip

Closes #119
Drop support for Python 3.4 (EOL 2019-03-18)
Support nbformat 2 notebooks without cell metadata
Ignore warnings from nbformat.{read,write}
fix attempting to install on python2
nbstripout >= 0.3.8 is Python 3 only #128
Set long_description_content_type to text/x-rst
Bump version: 0.3.7 → 0.3.8
Drop Python 2 support
Update badges
Drop 2.7 and 3.3 from AppVeyor, add 3.7 and 3.8
Test Python 3.7 / 3.8 with Travis, drop 2.7
Fix flake8 lint errors
Update changelog

Make --global commands independent of git repo

`nbstripout --{install,uninstall,status} --global` can now be run
outside a git repository.

Fixes #123
Document which metadata is stripped by default

Strip execution timing from cell metadata

Closes #118
add newline param to open and TextIOWrapper method
Nicer error message when input file is not found

Clean up error handling, closes #124

* Always check for `FileNotFoundError` when running git commands to
  handle case where git is not found.
* Remove special case for Windows by using `FileNotFoundError` instead
  of more general `OSError`.
* Do not require git to be present when running main action.
Document keep_output tag in README, closes #117
Update changelog

Support specifying keep_output as a cell tag (#120)

* fixes to keep_output as cell tag pull request
* refactored MetadataError
* read test artifacts from absolute path of test folder
